      "id": 1,
      "text": "Hawthorne was officially incorporated as a borough in 1898, though its roots stretch back to Dutch settlers in the 1700s.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5,
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://lambertcastle.org/an-early-history-of-hawthorne-new-jersey/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The borough’s name may honor author Nathaniel Hawthorne or simply describe the hawthorn bushes that once covered local pastures.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.hawthornenj.org/206/History"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Before becoming Hawthorne, the area was part of Manchester Township, which later split into several New Jersey boroughs including Haledon and Totowa.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        29
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://lambertcastle.org/an-early-history-of-hawthorne-new-jersey/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "During the Revolutionary War, Major General Lafayette is believed to have camped in the Hawthorne area.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        30
